additional_info:
If your Tomato router is not on 192.168.1.1, change the style to reflect it's address. If you have two or more Tomato installs on the same network, you can stack their addresses.

example:
@-moz-document domain("192.168.1.1"), domain("192.168.1.40") {

css:
@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);

@-moz-document domain("192.168.1.1") {

#container {
 background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #FFF;
 border-spacing: 0px;
 width: 100%;
 margin: 2px auto 50px;
}
}
